thread.title: Tracking Hurricane Joaquin

author: democratandchronicle.com
title: Tracking Hurricane Joaquin
text:
BUFFALO, NY-- Hurricane Joaquin is currently churning in the tropical Atlantic Ocean and its forecast to make a turn towards the United States. There is a chance this Category 1 hurricane could strengthen into a Category 3 storm in the next few days with winds in excess of 100 mph.
While there is a chance this storm remains out to sea there is a growing concern for a direct hit on the US this weekend.
The entirety of the Eastern Seaboard is threatened as the storm could make landfall anywhere from North Carolina to New York City.
Around here in Western New York the impacts will be nothing like what may happen along the coast but, clouds and rain may dampen our weekend as a result of this storm.
